                        <span class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight pr-4">What is the mind mapping feature and how does it help?</span>
                        <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="faq-icon w-6 h-6 text-red-500 flex-shrink-0 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer hidden px-8 md:px-12 pb-6 md:py-8 border-t border-gray-700">
                        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed text-lg">
                            Mind mapping is a visual thinking tool that helps you organize complex information hierarchically. In the context of law, it allows you to break down cases, arguments, and legal concepts into manageable pieces. You can see how different legal principles connect, organize evidence and arguments, and visualize the relationships between different elements of your case. This visual approach helps many people understand and retain legal information more effectively than traditional text-based learning.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
